Sources - The input data to be transferred.
Transformations - Various operations that you can apply to data as it streams through the data flow.
Sinks - Target in which the data will be loaded.

Running a pipeline can happen when:

1) Immediately
2) At explicitly scheduled intervals
3) In response to an event, such as new data files being added to a folder in a data lake.

